            <title>[THRIFT-1701] node.js TBufferedTransport buffer corruption</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1701</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Node&apos;s Buffer.copy&apos;s 3rd and 4th arguments are the start and end indexes to copy. There are two callers in the nodejs implementation of TBufferedTransport that pass a length instead of an end index as the 4th argument.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://nodejs.org/api/buffer.html#buffer_buf_copy_targetbuffer_targetstart_sourcestart_sourceend&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://nodejs.org/api/buffer.html#buffer_buf_copy_targetbuffer_targetstart_sourcestart_sourceend&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
